{
 "name": "RPlog_Trouble_on_Palanhi",
 "title": "Trouble on Palanhi: Holding the Black Dragon",
 "summary": "Aboard the YT-1300 Black Dragon docked at Palanhi, the archaeologist Paul Nighman wakes tangled with the teenage Shenner after carrying her back exhausted the night before, an awkward intimacy that leaves both shaken. The crisis deepens as word spreads that Jessalyn has been captured by Sabbath and taken offworld, Han Solo has vanished, and the Empire is closing in on the planet. A long, tense standoff plays out at the ship's airlock as Paul, Shenner, Amylynn, Tand, Tacra, Princess Leia, and Lando Calrissian argue over who should risk leaving the ship to search, with Paul repeatedly blocking the controls to stop Leia from going alone. Luke Skywalker returns only to insist on confronting Sabbath alone, refusing all offers of backup before departing in his X-wing once Lando reveals Jessalyn is held aboard Sabbath's ship in orbit. Lando secretly stays behind on his own business, asking Paul to cover for him and look after Leia, and the night ends with Paul and Shenner sharing a quiet, reassuring moment as they take turns guarding the ramp.",
